  "prompt": "How much time does Deloitte generally takes to get back after interview?",
  "response": "The time Deloitte takes to get back after an interview can vary depending on several factors, such as the specific role, the level of the position, and the number of candidates. However, typically:\n\n1. Entry-level positions (campus recruitment):\n- Usually 1-2 weeks after the final interview\n- Sometimes within a week\n\n2. Experienced professional roles:\n- Generally 1-3 weeks after the final interview\n- Can extend up to 4-6 weeks in some cases\n\n3. Senior/Leadership positions:\n- May take longer, sometimes 4-8 weeks\n\nFactors affecting response time:\n- Number of interview rounds\n- Complexity of the role\n- Internal decision-making processes\n- Current hiring needs\n\nTips:\n- It's acceptable to follow up politely after 1-2 weeks if you haven't heard back\n- Each hiring process can be different\n- These are general timelines and can vary\n\nFor the most accurate information, it's best to:\n- Ask the recruiter about expected timelines during the interview process\n- Check with the specific Deloitte office or team you interviewed with",
